                        angular <material>black</material> nasta‘līq hand. </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
                     <label>Marginalia:</label> Notes in various hands in the margins throughout.<lb/>
                     <label>Inscriptions:</label>The <locus from="ia" to="ia">fourth right flyleaf a
                        side (f. iva)</locus> bears an unsigned note by <persName role="ins fmo"
                        ref=" http://viaf.org/viaf/102326800" key="person_102326800">Sir William
                        Jones (1746–1794)</persName> declares that <persName role="fmo"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/53157628" key="person_53157628">Thomas Law
                        (1756–1834)</persName> presented it to the <orgName
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/155396778" key="person_155396778">Asiatick
                        Society</orgName> in <placeName
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7030776">Calcutta (Kolkata)</placeName>:<lb/>
                     <q xml:lang="en">Given to the Asiatick Society by Tho<hi rend="superscript"
                           >s</hi>. Law Esq.</q><lb/> A second pencilled autograph of former owner
                        <persName role="fmo ato ins" key="person_f3620">Samuel Hawtayne
